    <string name="large_text">
        This really great TED talk I came across, \'On Being Wrong\'.
        The speaker asks a very beautiful question - How does it feel to be wrong?
        Most people answered what I would have answered - dreadful, guilty, funny etc. But,
        then her take on it was really insightful. Rather than taking away from the speaker,
        how about you watch it and tell me what you think about how we as humans think about
        being wrong? This would be a fun little topic.
    </string>

